cribes. I'd classify this as critical since it directly affects how someone would implement the feature.\n\nNow I'm also checking the s2 message table for method 1—the knowledge file shows fewer property entries than expected. I'm noticing the source text gets cut off mid-sentence in the selection criteria section, but the key point seems to be about why the second method (automatic entity generation) is preferred in typical applications for productivity and quality reasons, while the first method has constraints on message ID structure. Let me compile my final findings on what's been fabricated or significantly simplified in the knowledge file. ナレーションの表現は少し曖昧だけど、エンティティ自動生成のメリットという本質は捉えている。ただ重大な問題を発見した—知識ファイルではFormクラスのFQNを指定するとあるが、ソースではクラス名だけを使っており、FQNを使うと動作が正しくなくなる可能性がある。この矛盾の深刻度を判断する必要がある。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19086,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19086,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0de16042-7da8-4813-bf8a-d6f010800b7f","uuid":"41dde957-04bf-437d-8d46-37b699ad4327"}
